T1  - Rural and Urban Differences: One More Time
AU  - Castellano, John J.
Y1  - 1976/09/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255616
DO  - 10.5465/255616
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 495
EP  - 502
VL  - 19
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study which assessed the influence of an employee's rural-urban background on attitudinal and behavioral response. The research was set in a single industrial plant. All data were collected at the plant site during working hours. Biographical and attitudinal data were collected from plant workers using a questionnaire. Results found significant differences in the two populations on the bases of frequency of absences and rated performance. But most of difference are explainable by length of company service.
AB  - The article presents a study which assessed the influence of an employee's rural-urban background on attitudinal and behavioral response. The research was set in a single industrial plant. All data were collected at the plant site during working hours. Biographical and attitudinal data were collected from plant workers using a questionnaire. Results found significant differences in the two populations on the bases of frequency of absences and rated performance. But most of difference are explainable by length of company service.
