EP  - 449
VL  - 19
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Data from two organizations revealed no consistent effect of leader sex on either leader behavior or subordinate satisfaction. The results fit a pattern of research evidence that shows sex stereotypes may be important in some laboratory settings but not in long-term situations. Thus some laboratory findings may be artifactual.
