T1  - Ten Year Job Satisfaction Trends in a Stable Organization
AU  - Smith, Frank
AU  - Roberts, Karlene H.
AU  - Hulin, Charles L.
Y1  - 1976/09/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255611
DO  - 10.5465/255611
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 462
EP  - 469
VL  - 19
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article focuses on a study which examined job satisfaction trends in a stable organization in the U.S. setting. The study reported is a large-scale, quasi-longitudinal, cross-sectional investigation. Geographical location of the respondent, job function and job tenure were the variables selected for the study which were related to the aspects of job satisfaction. Study results are presented in terms of satisfaction trends over time. These results establish the existence of a downward trend in job satisfaction for workers who are fairly representative of the U.S. industrial employees.
AB  - The article focuses on a study which examined job satisfaction trends in a stable organization in the U.S. setting. The study reported is a large-scale, quasi-longitudinal, cross-sectional investigation. Geographical location of the respondent, job function and job tenure were the variables selected for the study which were related to the aspects of job satisfaction. Study results are presented in terms of satisfaction trends over time. These results establish the existence of a downward trend in job satisfaction for workers who are fairly representative of the U.S. industrial employees.
